Costa Rica Consumer Prices Rose 0.25% in March From Month Ago

-- B y   E r i c   S a b o
-- 
2011-04-04T16:25:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/costa-rica-consumer-prices-rose-0-25-in-march-from-month-ago.html
Costa Rican consumer prices rose
0.25 percent in March from a month earlier, the national
statistics agency said on its website.  Prices rose 4.58 percent in March from a year earlier, the
agency said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Sabo in Panama City at 
 esabo1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  